    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"common good\" thing, but it feels like you're being pretty optimistic about the government being \"rigorous\" and \"respectful.\" in reality, if a group uses a religious exemption to deny services to certain people or skip out on civil rights laws, doesn't that make the religious group more important than the law itself? shouldn't the secular state's authority always come first to ensure everyone is treated equally?",
